I heard you're moving house next month! That is such a good news! I had moved from China all the way to Japan so I can definitely peovide you tons of advice!

Firstly, don't be worried about living and making friends in a new area. When I came to tokyo, I was so surprised by the local's heart-warming welcome, making freinds is so easy. You can be a potential popular student because of your unique identity, just be extrovert and make friends.

Secondly, living in a new area is a fresh experience. As an example, new parks to explore, new shopping malls to see. In my opinion, I see nearly no disadvantages on living in a new area. 

However, there are some concerns about bullying in some circumstances. I almost got bullied because I was Chinese, but it all settled down, and everything is back on track again, so it is also not a big deal.

All in all, just relax, everything will be fine and just relax and wait for your new journey to come!

